Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Registration has commenced ahead of the 2019 Basketball season for the Total National Division 1 and 2 Men’s leagues as well as the Zenith Women Basketball League. The registration for the Division 2 which started on Saturday, June 8 closes on June 17, while that for Division 1 and Zenith Women Basketball leagues closes on June 28. With 74 teams set for Division 2, state preliminaries will be played between June 21 and July 27, while the Zonal playoffs will be held between August 4 and 25 before going on a break for the FIBA Men’s World Cup and the Afrobasket for Women. The Conference playoffs will take place from October 18 to 27 before the National Finals coming up from November 11 to 18 after which four teams will be promoted to Division 1. The 12 teams in Division 1 will have their players’ registration through affiliated State Basketball Associations ahead of the conference playoffs starting from July 2 to 18. The National finals (Top 8) will run from September 16 and 30 at a venue to be decided by the NBBF. In the Zenith Women’s Basketball League, First Bank Club of Lagos will begin their title defence on July 1.